<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="40" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1050,1490]" pageId="6" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1237,1263]" pageId="6" pageNumber="40">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[343,676,1237,1262]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sternoptychidae" genus="Argyropelecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stomiiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hemigymnus">
<emphasis box="[343,676,1237,1262]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="40">Argyropelecus hemigymnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from its congeners by the following combination of characters: small size, rarely larger than 
<quantity box="[844,928,1274,1300]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="38.0">38 mm</quantity>
SL; trunk long and narrow; a single well developed post-abdominal spine, directed posteriorly, with both margins serrated.
</paragraph>
